      <BlogCrossLinks title="Scrabble Words Ending In J" />
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in J — The Rarest Category</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Words ending in J are the rarest ending category in Scrabble — even rarer than Q-endings. English almost never puts J at the end of a word. The few valid options are all loanwords from Arabic, Hindi, and Persian. Knowing these gives you a secret weapon most opponents have never seen.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">J tile value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL J-enders</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1 J-tile</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">All loanwords</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Origin</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">All Valid J-Ending Words (TWL)</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 TOP PLAY</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">HAJ</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">13 points · H(4)+A(1)+J(8) · Islamic pilgrimage to Mecca</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The highest-scoring J-ending word in TWL. A variant spelling of "hajj" (the pilgrimage). Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS. Quick 3-letter play that drops your J for 13 points.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">RAJ — 10 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">R(1)+A(1)+J(8). Rule or sovereignty (Hindi). The British Raj. Valid TWL + SOWPODS.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">TAJ — 10 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">T(1)+A(1)+J(8). A tall conical cap (Persian). As in Taj Mahal. Valid TWL + SOWPODS.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">SOWPODS-Only J-Ending Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-purple-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HAJJ</span><span class="text-purple-400 text-xs">21pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-purple-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HADJ</span><span class="text-purple-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Dictionary Difference</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">HAJJ (21pts) and HADJ (15pts) are <span class="text-white font-medium">only valid in SOWPODS</span> (international play). If you're playing TWL (North America), stick with HAJ, RAJ, and TAJ. Always know which dictionary your game uses before attempting these.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why J Rarely Ends English Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔍 Latin & Germanic roots</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">English inherited spelling from Latin and Germanic, where J didn't exist as a final letter. The /dʒ/ sound gets spelled -dge or -ge instead (edge, judge).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌍 All are loanwords</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Every J-ending Scrabble word comes from Arabic (haj, hajj), Hindi (raj), or Persian (taj). These languages commonly end words with the /dʒ/ sound spelled as J.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for J-Ending Plays</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">J-dump priority:</span> J is worth 8 points but extremely hard to use in longer words. HAJ (13pts) is your best quick dump — 3 tiles, 13 points, done. Don't hold J hoping for better when HAJ is available.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium square targeting:</span> J on DLS = 16 points from one tile. HAJ with J on DLS scores 21 total. Since J-ending words are short, you have flexibility to position J precisely on bonus squares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Surprise factor:</span> Most players don't know J-ending words exist. Playing TAJ or RAJ often draws challenges — and when opponents are wrong, you keep the points plus their turn. Psychological edge.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Better: Use J early</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">J is hard to use in bingos. Play HAJ/RAJ/TAJ quickly to free your rack for longer plays. 10-13 points for dumping J is excellent value.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Worse: Holding J too long</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">J blocks bingo potential and has limited combinations. Holding it for 3+ turns hoping for bigger play usually costs you more in lost rack flexibility.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

